<Requirements version="3" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.1 Explore Maze -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a top-level mission control state machine with at least the states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED} and deterministic transitions between them, such that:
(1) In the IDLE state, the state machine shall wait for receipt of an INIT_COMPLETED indication from the initialization module and then transition to EXPLORE.
(2) In the EXPLORE state, the state machine shall periodically request frontier targets from the frontier-generation module, request paths to the selected target from the path planner, and command the motion controller to execute the resulting motion primitives until either exploration completion or an exploration timeout event is received.
(3) In the RETURN_TO_START state, the state machine shall invoke the return-to-start service to compute a path to the start cell and shall command the motion controller to execute that path until the start cell is reached or a planning failure is reported.
(4) In the SECOND_RUN state, the state machine shall invoke the second-run planning service to compute the fastest path from the start cell to the goal region, shall command the motion controller to execute that path, and shall wait for receipt of a second-run status (success or failure).
(5) In the COMPLETED state, the state machine shall cease issuing new motion commands and maintain the final second-run status for external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall cause the mission control state machine to enter the EXPLORE state automatically when, within the periodic control loop, the initialization module has signaled INIT_COMPLETED and the sensor abstraction layer has provided at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared measurements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Stop Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall terminate the EXPLORE state and initiate RETURN_TO_START when either:
(1) the map completeness condition defined by the grid map module indicates that no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains in the UNKNOWN state, or
(2) the global exploration time limit defined in the time-limit requirement has been reached,
whichever condition is signaled first by the corresponding modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-based exploration strategy in the EXPLORE state such that the mission control state machine selects as navigation targets cells that are currently classified as UNKNOWN but are adjacent (in the 4-neighborhood) to at least one FREE cell in the internal grid map and requests paths to these targets from the path planner.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Generation Module</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-generation module that, upon request from the mission control state machine or planner, returns the set of all cells whose state is UNKNOWN and that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell in the grid map, and shall recompute this set whenever the classification of any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE or BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Target Selection Heuristic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall prioritize exploration frontier targets using a heuristic that:
(1) computes the estimated travel-time component using the same cell-to-cell traversal cost model defined in the path optimality criterion requirement, and
(2) adds a term that prefers frontiers expected to increase the number of newly observable cells,
and shall select targets that minimize this combined heuristic while ensuring that the estimated time to reach and explore the target does not exceed the remaining exploration time defined by the time-aware planning requirement.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.2 Wall Detection -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Wall Detection From Ultrasonic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret a front ultrasonic distance measurement d as a front wall in the current maze cell if the closed interval [d-12 cm, d+12 cm], derived from the ultrasonic uncertainty model, intersects the expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval for the current cell and pose that is computed from the 17.2 cm cell size and the 11 cm robot diameter.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Side Wall Detection From IR</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret an active obstacle indication from a left or right infrared sensor as a wall located along the corresponding side of the current maze cell if the robot’s pose is aligned to the maze axes within a configurable angular tolerance not exceeding 10 degrees.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Thresholding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis to filtered ultrasonic distance measurements to distinguish between free space and wall presence, such that single-sample noise or transient spikes do not cause flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuvers</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall command motor speeds to execute avoidance maneuvers (such as stopping and turning, or arc turns) when front or side wall detections indicate that the predicted robot trajectory would intersect a wall within one cell length, and shall select maneuvers that respect the robot footprint and minimum clearance margin so that collisions are prevented while maintaining progress toward exploration or path-planning goals.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.3 Create Map -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an in-memory grid map data structure representing the 4x8 maze, where each cell and each inter-cell wall segment is explicitly stored with its classification and can be addressed by integer coordinates (row, column) aligned with the assumed physical maze geometry.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell and Wall Update From Sensors</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall update the grid map cells and wall segments based on processed ultrasonic and infrared measurements obtained while the pose-estimation module indicates that the robot is located at a cell center or during a transition between adjacent cell centers, marking corresponding walls as PRESENT or ABSENT and updating adjacent cells as FREE if traversed without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initialize all cells and wall segments in the 4x8 grid map to an UNKNOWN classification at system startup prior to any sensor-based observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall designate a fixed coordinate in the grid map as the start cell at initialization, set its classification to FREE, and maintain a record of this coordinate for use in return-to-start and second-run behaviors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat once-observed wall and free classifications in the grid map as immutable for the duration of a mission, such that:
(1) cell states may change only from UNKNOWN to FREE or UNKNOWN to BLOCKED and shall not revert to UNKNOWN within a mission, and
(2) wall segment states may change only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or UNKNOWN to ABSENT and shall not change between PRESENT and ABSENT or revert to UNKNOWN within a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Completeness Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define the map as complete when no cell and no inter-cell wall segment in the grid map remains in the UNKNOWN state, and shall provide a boolean indication of this condition to the mission control state machine.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.7">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a grid map access interface that offers:
(1) functions to query the classification of any cell and wall segment by (row, column) indices,
(2) functions to update the classification of cells and wall segments, and
(3) an event mechanism or callback registration by which other modules can be notified when specific cells or walls change classification,
and shall ensure that all map queries, updates, and classification-change notifications occur within the context of the periodic control loop execution so that map access is single-threaded and does not require additional synchronization.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.4 Cell Classification -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each maze cell’s state using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}, shall ensure that each cell in the grid map is always in exactly one of these states, and shall allow cell state transitions only from UNKNOWN to FREE or from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED during a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Segment Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each wall segment between adjacent cells using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}, and shall allow wall segment state transitions only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or from UNKNOWN to ABSENT during a mission, so that once a wall is classified as PRESENT or ABSENT it shall not change state or revert to UNKNOWN in that mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free Cell Confirmation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a cell as FREE when the robot has successfully traversed into the cell without detecting a collision or blocking wall on the entry face, and no contradictory evidence, as defined by the sensor consistency-check requirement, has been accumulated for that cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Cell Inference</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a neighboring cell as BLOCKED if a wall segment between the current cell and that neighbor is classified as PRESENT, and shall never issue movement commands that attempt to enter a cell classified as BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.5 Time Constraint -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Global Mapping Time Limit</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a global time limit of 5 minutes from the start of exploration, after which it shall cease further exploration moves and signal to the mission control state machine that a timeout condition has occurred to initiate RETURN_TO_START, regardless of mapping completeness.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time-Aware Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall estimate remaining exploration time based on elapsed time and a configurable parameter representing the nominal time to traverse one cell at exploration speed, and shall avoid selecting exploration targets that cannot be reasonably reached and mapped before the 5 minute exploration time limit.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Nominal Cell Traversal Duration Parameter</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain a configurable parameter representing the nominal time required to traverse one maze cell at exploration speed, expressed in milliseconds, and shall make this parameter available to time-aware planning and exploration modules for remaining-time estimation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--PLAN--1.1 Path Planning -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a cell-based path planning algorithm (such as Dijkstra or A*) operating on the 4x8 grid map, where nodes correspond to FREE cells and edges connect orthogonally adjacent FREE cells (4-connected grid) that are not separated by PRESENT walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define path optimality as minimizing total traversal cost, where each move between orthogonally adjacent FREE cells has a non-negative cost that may be parameterized to distinguish straight-travel and turning penalties, and shall compute paths that minimize the sum of such costs between a given start and goal region.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat the selected 2x2 goal region as a set of up to four FREE goal cells and shall compute an optimal path from a given start cell to any of these goal cells, selecting the path with minimal traversal cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.7</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall recompute planned paths whenever newly acquired map information marks previously assumed FREE cells or ABSENT walls as BLOCKED or PRESENT and the current path would otherwise traverse those blocked cells or walls, using the grid map access interface to detect invalidation events.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Failure Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect and signal a planning failure when no path exists between the current cell and the desired target or goal region in the current map, so that higher-level logic can report failure or select alternative behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.1 Return to Start -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--EVENT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a return-to-start service that, when invoked by the mission control state machine after receipt of either an EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event or an EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event, computes a path from the robot’s current cell to the designated start cell using the path planning algorithm and current grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the computed return path cell by cell by issuing motor speed commands that move the robot between cell centers using motion primitives, while monitoring sensors to avoid collisions and triggering replanning if the path becomes invalid due to updated map information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.2 Second Run and HL--RUN--1.3 Efficient Path Execution -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initiate the SECOND_RUN state in the mission control state machine after the robot has returned to the start cell and exploration has been declared complete by the exploration module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fastest Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compute the fastest path from the start cell to the selected goal region using the grid map and path planner by configuring the traversal cost model parameters so that the resulting path minimizes an estimate of physical travel time during the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fast Path Motion Profile</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the fastest path using motor speed commands that increase translational speed relative to exploration while limiting the commanded speeds to computed maximum permissible values that ensure the robot can safely stop before a wall given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Success Criteria</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall declare the second run a success when the robot reaches any FREE cell in the 2x2 goal region following the fastest path without any detected collision; otherwise it shall declare the second run a failure.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Status Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a boolean or enumerated status output indicating success or failure of the second run upon completion or abort of the SECOND_RUN state for use by the mission control state machine and external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.1 Collision Avoidance -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Minimum Wall Clearance</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a configurable minimum clearance margin M &gt; 0 cm between the robot’s circular footprint of radius 5.5 cm and any wall position derived from the grid map, where M shall be selected to cover estimated worst-case pose and wall localization errors based on the ultrasonic uncertainty model, and shall ensure that planned and executed trajectories do not violate this clearance when following ideal commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop on Imminent Collision</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall immediately command both motors to speed 0 by invoking the motor command interface if filtered sensor data indicates an obstacle or wall within a configurable emergency distance threshold shorter than the nominal stopping distance at the current speed, and shall not resume movement until a new safe trajectory has been established.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.2 Sensor Noise Handling -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Sampling and Filtering</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall sample ultrasonic and infrared sensors at a configurable rate in the range [10, 50] Hz, with a default value of 20 Hz and timing jitter not exceeding a specified tolerance, and shall apply temporal filtering (such as moving average or median filters) to the sampled data to reduce the effect of random noise before using the data for wall detection or planning decisions, and shall perform this sampling once per iteration of the periodic control loop.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Consistency Checks on Sensor Data</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compare new sensor-based wall observations against existing map entries and shall treat large, isolated discrepancies as potential sensor errors, requiring at least N configurable consecutive sensor readings that indicate a wall where the map currently stores FREE or ABSENT before changing the established wall or cell classification, where N shall be an integer greater than or equal to 2 with a documented default value of 3 and a recommended configuration range 2 ≤ N ≤ 10.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.1 Sensor Processing -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Abstraction Layer</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a sensor abstraction layer that wraps the ultrasonic_get_distance and infrared_get_dsl_status/infrared_get_dsr_status functions and exposes normalized sensor data structures to higher-level modules, including for each control cycle:
(1) an ultrasonic measurement represented as (distance_cm, timestamp), where distance_cm is a float in centimeters in the robot-forward frame, and
(2) infrared measurements represented as (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp), where each flag is a binary obstacle indication and timestamp is the acquisition time.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Invalid Sensor Reading Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect invalid or out-of-range sensor return values, such as negative distances or implementation-specific saturation codes, and shall ignore these readings or replace them with safe default estimates rather than using them directly for mapping or control decisions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.2 Actuator Control -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Motor Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall control the differential drive motors exclusively via the function motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed), using integer speed values in the range [0,100] for each motor, and shall invoke motor_set at most once per iteration of the periodic control loop at the control loop frequency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Command Rate Limiting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall limit the rate of change of successive motor_set speed commands by enforcing configurable maximum increments per control cycle for left and right speeds to avoid abrupt accelerations or decelerations that could cause wheel slippage or loss of control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--2.1, 2.2, 2.3 Ultrasonic -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, once per sensor sampling period defined by the noise-handling requirement and synchronized with the periodic control loop, call ultrasonic_get_distance() and interpret the returned float value as the distance in centimeters to the nearest front obstacle along the sensor beam in the robot-forward frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Uncertainty Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model each ultrasonic distance measurement as having an uncertainty interval of at least ±12 cm around the measured distance value and shall incorporate this interval into wall distance estimation, collision risk computations, and clearance-margin evaluations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--3.x IR sensors -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, at each sensor sampling period synchronized with the periodic control loop, call infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() and interpret each returned uint8_t value as a binary obstacle detection flag for the respective left and right infrared sensors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Effective Range Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall assume that a positive obstacle indication from an infrared sensor corresponds to an obstacle located approximately 4 cm from the sensor along its measurement direction and shall use this nominal distance when inferring side wall positions in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Orientation Compensation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall account for the approximately 25 degree mounting angle of each infrared sensor relative to the robot front direction when transforming infrared obstacle detections into equivalent lateral wall distances and positions in the maze reference frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--1.1 Robot Shape -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Robot Footprint Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model the robot as a circle of radius 5.5 cm when checking for possible collisions with walls located at cell boundaries spaced approximately 17.2 cm apart and when evaluating clearance against the minimum clearance margin.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.1 Differential Drive -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Differential Drive Kinematics</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement kinematic equations for a differential drive robot to estimate changes in robot orientation and position over time based on the left and right motor speed commands and the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration from the scheduling module, without assuming constant rotational speed.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Center Motion Primitives</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide motion primitives that move the robot from one maze cell center to an adjacent cell center and turn in place to discrete headings aligned with maze axes, using sequences of motor_set commands whose durations and speeds are derived from the differential-drive kinematics and cell dimension of approximately 17.2 cm.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.3 Translational Velocity -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Limitation for Safety</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall constrain the commanded motor speeds such that the resulting translational speed does not exceed a configured maximum below the 200 cm/s hardware capability, where this maximum speed is computed to ensure that, given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty, the robot can safely stop before reaching a detected wall.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--ENV--1.x Maze properties -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Coordinate System</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define a grid coordinate system with 4 rows and 8 columns for the maze, with a consistent convention for mapping physical positions to cell indices, such as defining row 0, column 0 as the start cell, and shall use this convention consistently across mapping, planning, and control modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use the approximate cell dimension of 17.2 cm when transforming between estimated traveled distances and transitions between maze cell centers for pose estimation, motion primitive generation, and grid map updates.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use an approximate wall thickness of 1.6 cm when reasoning about the physical extent of walls relative to the robot footprint in collision and clearance checks.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Inter-Cell Wall Indexing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall index possible wall positions as boundaries between horizontally and vertically adjacent cells and shall store wall presence or absence for each such boundary in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, upon completion of exploration, identify as candidate goal regions all contiguous 2x2 blocks of cells that are all classified as FREE and reachable from the start cell in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, when multiple candidate 2x2 FREE regions exist, select as the maze goal region the one that minimizes the optimal path cost from the start cell according to the traversal cost metric defined for the path planner, and shall provide this selected region to the second-run planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Additional LLRs -->

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Level Pose Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an estimate of the robot’s current maze cell index (row, column) and discrete heading aligned with the maze axes, updated in each control loop cycle by integrating the differential drive kinematics over the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration provided by the scheduling module and the issued motor speed commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose Correction Using Map Features</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall correct accumulated orientation and position error in the pose estimate when the robot is aligned with maze axes and wall detections indicate proximity to known cell boundaries, by snapping the estimated heading to the nearest axis-aligned direction and adjusting the position to the nearest cell center consistent with the wall observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Center Entry Notification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect when the pose estimate crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center and shall notify the mapping module of the new current cell index so that cell and wall updates can be associated with the correct cell transition.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--EVENT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Status Events</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an exploration-status module, integrated with the mission control state machine, that publishes EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events by enqueuing corresponding event records into a system event queue accessible to the mission control and return-to-start modules when, respectively, the map completeness criterion indicates a complete map or the global exploration time limit is reached.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--SCHED--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Periodic Control Loop Scheduling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a periodic control loop with a configurable period T such that the control loop frequency equals the sensor sampling rate defined in the sensor sampling requirement, and in each cycle it shall:
(1) acquire sensor readings via the sensor abstraction layer,
(2) update the grid map using the mapping module,
(3) update the mission control state machine,
(4) compute or update the current path as required by the active state, and
(5) issue motor_set commands via the motion control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INIT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Initialization Completion Signaling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an initialization module that, after all required hardware and software initialization routines have successfully completed, sets an INIT_COMPLETED flag or publishes an INIT_COMPLETED event within the main execution context, and the mission control state machine shall only transition from IDLE to EXPLORE after this indication is present.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>
<Design>
    <Components version="1">
        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--1</ID>
            <Name>Mission Control State Machine</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Central mission coordinator that owns the top-level mission state machine and orchestrates exploration, return-to-start, and second run behaviors.
                Responsibilities:
                - Maintain mission state with states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - Consume initialization, exploration-status, planning, and second-run status indications.
                - Periodically trigger frontier target selection, path planning, and motion execution based on current state.
                - Enforce exploration start/stop conditions, including sensor-availability and time-limit conditions.
                - Invoke return-to-start and second-run services and relay their status to external reporting.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request sent in EXPLORE to frontier-generation module to compute or refresh the current set of frontier cells.
                                Contains: current robot cell index (row, col), current mission time, and remaining exploration time (ms).
                                Triggered once per exploration control cycle where target reselection is required.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierTargetSelectionContext</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional context information for frontier target selection, including:
                                - Current cell index.
                                - Current goal region, if known.
                                - Nominal cell traversal duration.
                                Intended to allow frontier module or associated heuristic to compute expected information gain and feasibility.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathPlanningRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request to path planner to compute a path for:
                                - Exploration navigation to a selected frontier target cell (EXPLORE state).
                                - Return-to-start path (RETURN_TO_START state).
                                - Second-run fastest path (SECOND_RUN state).
                                Fields:
                                - RequestID.
                                - Mode: {EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN}.
                                - StartCell (row, col).
                                - GoalSpec: single goal cell or goal region set.
                                - TraversalCostProfileID (points to cost parameters for exploration or second-run).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion command to motion control / motion primitive module.
                                Encodes:
                                - Path to execute (list of cell centers) or next motion primitive.
                                - Execution mode: {ExplorationSpeed, ReturnSpeed, SecondRunSpeed}.
                                - Safety constraints: min clearance M, emergency stop thresholds.
                                Generated each control loop when in EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, or SECOND_RUN and a valid path exists.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunStatusOutput</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated status output for external reporting:
                                Values: {NOT_STARTED, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILURE, ABORTED_TIMEOUT, ABORTED_COLLISION}.
                                Updated when entering SECOND_RUN, on completion, or on abort.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FGM_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Set of frontier cells computed by frontier-generation module.
                                Structure: list of (row, col) cells that are UNKNOWN and 4-neighbors of FREE cells.
                                Includes timestamp and map revision number to detect stale data.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PathPlanningResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response from path planner:
                                - RequestID echo.
                                - Status: {SUCCESS, FAILURE_NO_PATH, FAILURE_TIMEOUT, INVALID_GOAL}.
                                - Path: ordered list of cell indices.
                                - EstimatedTravelCost and EstimatedTravelTime.
                                Used by mission control to command motion or handle planning failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_COMPLETED</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag or event from initialization module indicating successful completion of system initialization.
                                Sampled each control loop while in IDLE.
                                Mission control uses this along with valid sensor data to transition to EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ExplorationEvents</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Events from exploration-status module:
                                - EXPLORATION_COMPLETED: map completeness achieved.
                                - EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT: global mapping time limit reached.
                                These events are enqueued into a system event queue; mission control drains the queue once per control loop and updates state accordingly.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ReturnToStartStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status from return-to-start service/motion execution:
                                - {RUNNING, REACHED_START, PLANNING_FAILURE, ABORTED_COLLISION}.
                                Mission control uses this to determine when to initiate SECOND_RUN or declare failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SecondRunExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status from second-run execution logic:
                                - {RUNNING, SUCCESS_REACHED_GOAL, FAILURE_COLLISION, FAILURE_NO_PATH}.
                                Mission control propagates this into COMPLETED state and MC_SecondRunStatusOutput.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SensorAvailabilityStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean from sensor abstraction layer indicating that at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared measurements has been acquired in current mission.
                                Used along with INIT_COMPLETED to trigger transition from IDLE to EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current discrete pose estimate: (row, col, headingIndex).
                                Used in EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN to determine start cell for path planning and to detect arrival at target cells or goal region cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GoalRegionInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected 2x2 goal region for second run:
                                - Set of 1–4 FREE goal cells (row, col).
                                - Region ID and metadata.
                                Provided upon exploration completion and prior to SECOND_RUN state planning.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_StateBroadcast</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Broadcast of current mission state for logging or visualization:
                                {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                                Emitted each control loop or on state changes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_Timebase</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Control loop tick and elapsed mission time from scheduler.
                                Includes:
                                - Loop index.
                                - ElapsedTimeMs since exploration start.
                                Used internally to enforce timing behavior and exploration time limits.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Executed once per iteration of the periodic control loop (CMP--10), after sensor acquisition and map update, before motion output.
                Conditions:
                - System is running (not in hardware-level fault).
                - INIT_COMPLETED flag available for IDLE-&gt;EXPLORE.
                - Uses exploration events, planner responses, and motion status to drive deterministic transitions between mission states.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Invoked exactly once per control loop with period T defined by scheduler (LL--SCHED--1.1.1).
                - EXPLORE behavior: frontier requests and planning requests are limited to at most one per control loop but may be throttled (e.g., only when previous path has been consumed or invalidated).
                - RETURN_TO_START and SECOND_RUN: planning invoked once per entry; replanning invoked when map invalidations arise.
                - All decisions must complete within the control loop budget; mission control logic is O(1) to O(N_frontiers) per cycle, where N_frontiers is bounded by 32 cells in a 4x8 grid.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Mission state is always one of {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - State transitions are deterministic for a given history of events and time.
                - While in COMPLETED, no new motion commands are issued to motion control.
                - While in IDLE, motors remain stopped except for test routines external to this component.
                - Only one of EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, or SECOND_RUN can be active at a time.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning failure in RETURN_TO_START:
                  Trigger: PL_PathPlanningResponse with FAILURE_NO_PATH or FAILURE_TIMEOUT for return-to-start request.
                  Effect: Mission control records return failure, may either:
                    * Transition directly to COMPLETED with MC_SecondRunStatusOutput=FAILURE, or
                    * Remain in RETURN_TO_START and request retry with backoff (implementation policy encoded via AdditionalData).
                - Planning failure in SECOND_RUN:
                  Trigger: PL_PathPlanningResponse with FAILURE_NO_PATH or FAILURE_TIMEOUT for second-run request.
                  Effect: MC_SecondRunStatusOutput=FAILURE; transition to COMPLETED.
                - Exploration timeout:
                  Trigger: EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event prior to EXPLORATION_COMPLETED.
                  Effect: EXPLORE-&gt;RETURN_TO_START, with cause logged as TIMEOUT; second run still attempted if return succeeds.
                - Unexpected event in COMPLETED:
                  Any further exploration or planning events are ignored; MC_SecondRunStatusOutput remains latched.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.1.2 LL--RUN--1.2.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3 LL--RUN--1.2.4 LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--2</ID>
            <Name>Frontier Generation and Exploration Target Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides frontier-based exploration capabilities:
                - Maintains and computes frontier cells based on current grid map.
                - Offers functions to retrieve current frontier set.
                - Implements heuristic to prioritize frontier targets using estimated travel-time and expected information gain.
                - Enforces time-aware filtering of candidate targets based on remaining exploration time and nominal cell traversal duration.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FGM_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Set of frontier cells: UNKNOWN cells that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell.
                                Represented as vector of (row, col).
                                Recomputed:
                                - On demand (MC_FrontierRequest).
                                - Whenever a cell transitions from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED or a wall changes classification, via map-change notifications.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FGM_SelectedTarget</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Single frontier cell chosen as exploration target based on heuristic.
                                Structure:
                                - TargetCell (row, col).
                                - EstimatedTravelTimeMs.
                                - EstimatedNewlyObservableCells.
                                - CompositeHeuristicValue.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger from mission control to update frontier set and provide a new frontier target.
                                Includes: current robot cell, remaining exploration time, and cost profile ID.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries to grid map:
                                - GetCellState(row, col) -&gt; {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                                - GetNeighborCells4(row, col) -&gt; list of valid neighbor indices.
                                - GetWallState between cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>TimeAwarePlanningInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                RemainingTimeMs and NominalCellTraversalDurationMs from time-constraint module.
                                Used to discard frontier candidates whose estimated travel time + mapping overhead exceeds RemainingTimeMs.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FGM_TargetEstimates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each frontier candidate, FGM can optionally expose:
                                - Estimated path cost and time using current path cost model.
                                - Estimated information gain (number of UNKNOWN cells likely to be observed from that cell, constrained by sensor ranges).
                                Returned for debugging or to allow planner to participate in target selection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_TravelTimeEstimates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Helper interface from path planner used when FGM requests approximate costs to a set of frontier cells without computing full individual paths (e.g., multi-goal heuristics).
                                Encodes estimated traversal times by reusing path cost metric.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Executed in two contexts:
                - On-demand: when MC_FrontierRequest is received within EXPLORE, FGM recomputes the frontier set (if stale) and selects a target.
                - Incremental maintenance: subscribed to grid-map classification-change notifications (CMP--3) and updates cached frontier set whenever a cell state changes from UNKNOWN or walls change, to allow O(1) retrieval during MC_FrontierRequest.
                All operations occur inside the periodic control loop.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Frontier recomputation worst-case: scans 4x8 grid (32 cells) each time; negligible vs control loop period.
                - Target selection heuristic loops over at most N_frontiers &lt;= 32 candidates.
                - Triggered at most once per control loop for target selection; frontier set maintenance can occur multiple times per loop, but in practice limited by sensor update rate and smaller number of cell changes.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Frontier set contains only UNKNOWN cells.
                - Each frontier cell has at least one 4-neighbor classified FREE.
                - Selected target always belongs to current frontier set and satisfies remaining-time constraint.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No frontier cells available:
                  Trigger: FGM_FrontierSet empty.
                  Effect: FGM_SelectedTarget indicates no target; MC interprets this as exploration completion candidate. Exploration-status module will eventually publish EXPLORATION_COMPLETED based on map completeness.
                - Time-limit constraint violation:
                  Trigger: All frontier candidates have estimated travel time + mapping overhead &gt; RemainingTimeMs.
                  Effect: FGM_SelectedTarget reports no feasible targets; MC may continue short movements or immediately rely on exploration timeout event to transition to RETURN_TO_START.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4 LL--MAP--1.1.5 LL--MAP--1.1.6
                LL--MAP--1.1.6 LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--3</ID>
            <Name>Grid Map Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains the in-memory 4x8 grid map and associated wall segments, providing single-threaded access and update mechanisms:
                - Stores cell classification (UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED) and wall segment classification (UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT).
                - Initializes map and start cell.
                - Provides query and update operations.
                - Emits classification-change notifications.
                - Provides map completeness boolean for exploration logic.
                - Enforces immutability rules for classifications within a mission.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Map structure exposed to planning and exploration modules via interface functions:
                                - GetCellState(row, col).
                                - GetWallState(edgeIndex / (row, col, orientation)).
                                - GetNeighbors(row, col) considering map boundaries.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification event issued when a cell or wall segment changes classification.
                                Contains:
                                - Type: {CELL, WALL}.
                                - Indices.
                                - PreviousState and NewState.
                                Consumed by frontier-generation, replanning, and other modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_MapUpdateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Update requests from mapping module: mark cells FREE/BLOCKED and walls PRESENT/ABSENT based on sensor interpretation and pose.
                                Each request includes:
                                - Target indices.
                                - Requested new classification.
                                - Reason (e.g., cell traversed, wall detected).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag indicating whether map is complete:
                                - true: no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains UNKNOWN.
                                - false: otherwise.
                                Sampled by exploration-status module and mission control to decide exploration completion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Init_Request</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Initialization trigger received at system startup to:
                                - Initialize all cells and wall segments to UNKNOWN.
                                - Designate the fixed start cell and set it to FREE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Map initialization at startup:
                  1) Allocate cell array [4][8], initialize each cell state to UNKNOWN.
                  2) Allocate wall arrays for vertical and horizontal walls as per inter-cell wall indexing.
                  3) Mark designated start cell (e.g., (0,0)) as FREE.
                - During each control loop:
                  - Apply queued map update requests from mapping module (ensuring UNKNOWN-&gt;FREE/BLOCKED or UNKNOWN-&gt;PRESENT/ABSENT only).
                  - Trigger classification-change notifications for any changed entries.
                  - Recompute completeness lazily as needed or maintain counters of UNKNOWN cells/walls.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All map operations are performed inside the control loop context (single-threaded), as required by LL--MAP--1.3.7.
                - Worst-case map operations (scanning 32 cells and associated walls) are bounded and fast relative to T.
                - Completeness flag may be recomputed incrementally using maintained counts to ensure O(1) behavior per update.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Every cell state ∈ {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                - Every wall segment state ∈ {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - No cell reverts from FREE/BLOCKED to UNKNOWN and no wall reverts from PRESENT/ABSENT to UNKNOWN within a mission.
                - No cell or wall toggles between FREE/BLOCKED or PRESENT/ABSENT once set (monotonic classification).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Invalid classification transition:
                  Trigger: request to change from FREE/BLOCKED to another value or PRESENT/ABSENT to another value.
                  Handling: reject update and log diagnostic; preserve existing classification.
                - Out-of-range indices:
                  Trigger: requests referencing cells or walls outside 4x8 map.
                  Handling: discard update, log error.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.3.3 LL--MAP--1.3.4 LL--MAP--1.3.5 LL--MAP--1.3.6
                LL--MAP--1.3.7 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--MAP--1.4.3 LL--MAP--1.4.4
                LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--4</ID>
            <Name>Path Planner</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Implements cell-based path planning on the 4x8 grid map:
                - Provides Dijkstra or A* search to compute paths between cells and goal regions.
                - Supports configurable traversal cost parameters for exploration and second run.
                - Handles multiple-goal planning for 2x2 goal regions.
                - Supports replanning on map updates that invalidate current paths.
                - Reports planning failures to mission control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PathPlanningResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning result for a given request:
                                - RequestID.
                                - Status: SUCCESS or specific failure.
                                - Path: ordered list of cells from start to selected goal.
                                - TotalCost and optionally EstimatedTimeMs (TotalCost transformed via cost-to-time mapping).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PlanningFailureEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Simplified event to indicate no path exists given current map.
                                Used by mission control to trigger alternative behaviors.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathPlanningRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning request specifying:
                                - Mode {EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN}.
                                - Start cell and goal specification (single cell or list of goal cells for goal region).
                                - Traversal cost parameters ID.
                                - Optional limit on max allowed cost.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapReadAccess</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Access to grid map functions:
                                - Query cell and wall states to build navigation graph.
                                - Implement 4-connected neighbors only between FREE cells not separated by PRESENT walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning invalidation hook:
                                - When map changes mark cells from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED or walls UNKNOWN-&gt;PRESENT that intersect current path, planner flags current path as invalid.
                                - Planner notifies mission control or motion control about invalidation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_GoalRegionCostInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Intermediate data shared with goal-region selection:
                                - For each 2x2 FREE candidate region, path cost from start to each cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_GoalCells</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For second run, planner receives the selected goal region cells from goal-region selection module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On each planning request:
                  1) Build search graph implicitly using grid map cell states and wall states.
                  2) Apply Dijkstra or A* depending on configuration:
                     - Node = FREE cell.
                     - Edge exists for orthogonally adjacent FREE cells if there is no PRESENT wall between them.
                     - Edge cost determined from traversal cost model (straight and turn penalties).
                  3) For goal regions, treat each FREE goal cell as a possible terminal node; run multi-goal search or run algorithm once until all goals discovered.
                  4) On success, reconstruct path and compute total cost.
                  5) Map cost to time estimate using nominal cell traversal duration for derived heuristics.
                  6) Return PL_PathPlanningResponse.
                - Replanning:
                  - When GM_ClassificationChangeEvent arrives and current path intersects newly BLOCKED or wall PRESENT segments, invalidate current path and notify mission control.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Path planning executed within control loop but may be limited to one planning run per loop.
                - With 32 cells, worst-case Dijkstra/A* is small; implementation must ensure worst-case search finishes within T, or planning can span multiple loops with incremental expansion.
                - Replanning triggered only when path invalidation occurs to avoid unnecessary computations.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - No path includes BLOCKED cells or crosses PRESENT walls.
                - Edge costs are non-negative.
                - Returned path cost is minimal given the traversal cost model.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No path found:
                  Trigger: search exhausts all reachable cells without reaching any goal.
                  Effect: PL_PathPlanningResponse with Status=FAILURE_NO_PATH; mission control handles this (e.g., abort or alternative behavior).
                - Map inconsistent during planning:
                  Trigger: map changes while planning in progress.
                  Handling: either lock snapshot of map per planning run or restart planning with new map; only consistent snapshots used for final paths.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--PLAN--1.1.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.4 LL--PLAN--1.1.5
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--ENV--3.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--5</ID>
            <Name>Goal Region Identification and Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Determining and selecting the 2x2 goal region after exploration:
                - Identifies all candidate 2x2 regions composed entirely of FREE cells and reachable from start.
                - Requests path costs to each candidate from path planner.
                - Selects region with minimal optimal path cost.
                - Exposes chosen region to second-run planning and mission control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_CandidateRegions</Name>
                            <Description>
                                List of candidate 2x2 FREE regions:
                                - Each candidate: 4 cell indices (row, col) representing the region.
                                - Mark if reachable from start (using info from path planner or BFS).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Read-only snapshot of FREE/BLOCKED cell states to enumerate all 2x2 blocks and check classification.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_GoalRegionSelection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected goal region:
                                - Set of up to four FREE goal cells.
                                - Region ID and path cost.
                                Provided to planner for second-run fastest path computation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_GoalRegionCostInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each candidate region, cost of cheapest path from start cell to any of its 4 cells, using the traversal cost metric.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_SelectedGoalRegionInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Goal region exported to mission control for use in SECOND_RUN:
                                - Region cells.
                                - Chosen target goal cell (may be the one with minimum path cost).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ExplorationCompletedTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event from exploration-status/mission control indicating exploration is complete and goal region identification should execute exactly once.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On exploration completion:
                  1) Obtain map snapshot from grid map.
                  2) Enumerate all possible 2x2 blocks; for each, check all four cells are FREE.
                  3) For each all-FREE block, request path costs via path planner from start to each of the four cells.
                  4) Filter out non-reachable candidates (no path).
                  5) Select candidate whose minimal path cost is smallest.
                  6) Store and publish selected region.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Executed once after map completion detection.
                - With at most (3*7)=21 possible 2x2 blocks and 32 cells, enumeration and cost queries are trivial; must fit within several control loop cycles.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Selected goal region, if any, is reachable from start.
                - Selected region cost is minimal among reachable candidate regions based on traversal cost metric.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No 2x2 FREE reachable region:
                  Trigger: enumeration yields no candidate that is all FREE and reachable.
                  Effect: report failure condition to mission control; second run may be disabled or alternative criteria used (e.g., single goal cell).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--ENV--3.1.1 LL--ENV--3.1.2 LL--PLAN--1.1.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--6</ID>
            <Name>Mapping and Wall Detection Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Uses processed sensor data and pose estimation to update grid map cells and walls:
                - Interprets ultrasonic and infrared readings to detect front and side walls with uncertainty and hysteresis.
                - Executes wall proximity thresholding with hysteresis on ultrasonic data.
                - Generates collision avoidance triggers when trajectory intersects imminent walls.
                - Applies free cell confirmation and blocked cell inference rules.
                - Issues map update requests to grid map.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_MapUpdateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to grid map:
                                - Update wall segment classifications (PRESENT/ABSENT) on appropriate boundaries.
                                - Update cell classifications to FREE or BLOCKED.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellAndWallStates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current classification around robot:
                                - State of current cell, neighboring cells, and relevant walls.
                                Used for consistent updates and blocked cell inference.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interpreted wall detections relative to current cell:
                                - Flags for front, left, right wall presence.
                                - Estimated wall distances (with uncertainty intervals) in maze coordinates.
                                Used by motion control for avoidance and by pose correction.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_CollisionRiskEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event raised if predicted trajectory intersects a wall within one cell length, triggering avoidance maneuvers in motion control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered sensor data from sensor abstraction and filtering:
                                - Ultrasonic: (distance_cm, timestamp).
                                - IR: left_flag, right_flag, timestamp.
                                All invalid or out-of-range readings already sanitized.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Discrete pose estimate with cell-centered position and heading, plus flag indicating:
                                - AtCellCenter or InTransitionBetweenCells.
                                Used to decide when to update particular walls and cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Read filtered, validated sensor measurements and current pose.
                2) If pose aligned to maze axes within tolerance and at/near cell center:
                   - Use ultrasonic reading to check for front wall:
                     * Compute measurement interval [d-12, d+12] cm.
                     * Compute expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval (based on cell size 17.2 cm and robot radius 5.5 cm, plus wall thickness).
                     * If intervals intersect and past hysteresis thresholds confirm stable detection, mark front wall PRESENT.
                   - Use IR readings:
                     * If left_flag or right_flag active and pose heading within 10° tolerance, infer side wall presence:
                       - Account for 25° sensor mounting angle and 4 cm effective range and project to wall location on left/right boundary of current cell.
                       - Mark corresponding lateral walls PRESENT.
                3) If robot transitions between cell centers without collisions:
                   - Mark traversed cells as FREE once verified by sensor consistency checks.
                4) Apply wall proximity thresholding:
                   - Use configurable upper/lower thresholds on filtered ultrasonic distance to determine wall vs free.
                   - Maintain hysteresis state per direction to avoid flip-flopping.
                5) For any present wall between current and neighbor cell, mark neighbor cell BLOCKED and ensure no motion commands target it.
                6) Issue map update requests accordingly.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Invoked once per control loop after sensor filtering, before grid-map updates are applied.
                - Computations are simple algebra and local reasoning around at most a few walls; must complete within T.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Free cell confirmation only after successful traversal without collision and no conflicting evidence requiring N consecutive contradictions.
                - Blocked cell inference always consistent with wall segment state PRESENT.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Conflicting sensor data vs map:
                  Trigger: new sensor readings indicate a wall where map indicates FREE or ABSENT, but do not satisfy N consecutive readings threshold.
                  Handling: flagged as potential sensor error; map left unchanged until N readings accumulate.
                - Pose misalignment &gt; tolerance:
                  Trigger: robot heading deviates &gt;10° from maze axes.
                  Effect: IR-based side wall inference suppressed until pose is corrected.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.2.2 LL--MAP--1.2.3 LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.4.3 LL--MAP--1.4.4
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1 LL--INTERF--3.3.1 LL--INTERF--3.4.1
                LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--ENV--1.3.1 LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--7</ID>
            <Name>Sensor Abstraction and Filtering Layer</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Wraps raw sensor APIs and provides normalized, filtered sensor data:
                - Calls ultrasonic_get_distance and IR status functions at control loop frequency.
                - Detects and handles invalid/out-of-range sensor readings.
                - Applies temporal filtering (moving average/median) to reduce noise.
                - Provides unified ultrasonic and IR measurement structures to mapping and reliability modules.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SampledSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Raw per-cycle data from sensors:
                                - Ultrasonic distance (float cm).
                                - IR left/right flags (uint8_t to boolean).
                                - Timestamps.
                                Provided immediately after acquisition to filtering logic.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Tick from scheduler at frequency matching configured sensor sampling rate.
                                Used to ensure one sampling per iteration and enforce jitter constraints.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Normalized and filtered sensor data:
                                - Ultrasonic: (filteredDistance_cm, timestamp).
                                - IR: (filteredLeftFlag, filteredRightFlag, timestamp).
                                Filtering uses configured sampling rate (10–50 Hz, default 20 Hz) and temporal filtering method.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SensorAvailabilityStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag indicating that at least one valid (non-invalid) ultrasonic distance and both IR readings have been successfully acquired at least once since mission start.
                                Used by mission control to determine exploration start condition.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RawUltrasonicApi</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interface to ultrasonic_get_distance(), returning raw float distance or specific error/saturation codes.
                                SAL is responsible for interpreting invalid codes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RawIrApi</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interfaces to infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status().
                                Returns uint8_t for each sensor interpreted as binary detection flags.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) On Sched_ControlLoopTick, call ultrasonic_get_distance(), infrared_get_dsl_status(), infrared_get_dsr_status().
                2) Check for invalid values (negative distances, NaN, saturation codes):
                   - Replace invalid ultrasonic values with "no obstacle" default (e.g., beyond maze size plus uncertainty) and mark as invalid for mapping decisions.
                   - IR invalid values treated as no obstacle or flagged per configuration.
                3) Push readings into fixed-length buffers (size determined by filter window) and compute filtered values (moving average or median).
                4) Compose normalized structures with filtered values and current timestamp.
                5) Update SensorAvailabilityStatus if all required sensors have delivered at least one valid reading.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sampling exactly once per control loop iteration, at frequency in [10, 50] Hz.
                - Timing jitter limited by scheduler; SAL must not introduce additional variability.
                - Filtering operations O(windowSize) with small window sizes (e.g., 3–5 samples).
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - SAL never forwards raw invalid values to mapping or planning modules.
                - Filtered data is always defined (either from valid readings or safe defaults).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Persistent invalid ultrasonic reading:
                  Handling: maintain default "no obstacle" reading while flagging sensor degradation; mapping may rely more heavily on IR or map data.
                - Loss of IR data:
                  Handling: treat IR as inactive (no obstacle) but rely on ultrasonic and map to avoid collisions; log error.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.1.2 LL--INTERF--2.1.1 LL--INTERF--3.1.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--8</ID>
            <Name>Motion Control and Collision Avoidance</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Converts high-level path and motion primitives into motor_set commands with safety:
                - Executes cell-center motion primitives based on differential drive kinematics and cell geometry.
                - Enforces speed limitations, rate limiting, and emergency stop behavior.
                - Performs wall avoidance maneuvers when mapping reports imminent collisions.
                - Supports different speed profiles for exploration, return-to-start, and second run.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status of path execution:
                                - For return-to-start: RUNNING, REACHED_START, PATH_INVALID, COLLISION_ABORTED.
                                - For second run: RUNNING, SUCCESS_REACHED_GOAL, COLLISION_ABORTED.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion instruction from mission control including:
                                - Path (sequence of cells) or next cell target.
                                - Speed profile.
                                - Safety constraints.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EM_StopCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Implicit command to stop: invoked by motion control when emergency conditions occur.
                                This is not a signal to SAL but rather an invocation of motor_set(0,0); the signal is conceptual for design.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to monitor distance to obstacles for emergency-stop decisions based on configured emergency threshold and stopping distance.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Motion_MotorCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation of motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) with speeds in [0,100].
                                Enforced to be at most once per control loop, respecting rate limiting on speed increments.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Ensures motor commands are synchronized with control loop period T and updates internal timers for motion primitive durations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Motion_AvoidanceStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notifies mapping/mission control when avoidance maneuvers are in progress or completed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to predict trajectory-wall intersections within one cell length and trigger avoidance maneuvers before collision.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_CollisionRiskEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Direct event indicating imminent collision within one cell length; triggers avoidance or emergency stop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Read current MC_MotionCommand, SAL_FilteredSensorData, and MM_WallDetectionResult.
                2) If emergency condition:
                   - If any sensor indicates obstacle closer than emergency threshold &lt; nominal stopping distance (based on current speed and uncertainty):
                     * Immediately call motor_set(0,0).
                     * Set internal state to EMERGENCY_STOP.
                     * Do not resume movement until new safe path or motion command is provided.
                3) Else if MM_CollisionRiskEvent raised:
                   - Plan short avoidance maneuver (e.g., stop + in-place turn, or arc turn) such that:
                     * Robot footprint plus clearance M does not intersect any wall.
                     * Maneuver maintains or restores progress towards mission goal.
                4) If executing a cell-center motion primitive:
                   - Use differential drive kinematics with control-loop period to incrementally move between cell centers or rotate to discrete headings.
                   - Enforce speed limits:
                     * ExplorationSpeed &lt;= MaxSafeSpeedExploration.
                     * SecondRunSpeed &lt;= MaxSafeSpeedSecondRun &lt; hardware limit and derived from safety constraints.
                5) Before calling motor_set:
                   - Apply rate limiting to speed increments between consecutive cycles.
                6) Issue one motor_set per cycle with computed speeds.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Called once per control loop after mission control and path planning decisions.
                - Kinematic integration and collision checks use current T or measured cycle duration.
                - Emergency stop and avoidance decisions must be computed within one loop so that robot can stop within safe distance given sampling rate and uncertainties.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Rate of change of motor_set speeds per control cycle does not exceed configured maximum per wheel.
                - Commanded speeds never exceed configured safety maximum computed from sampling rate, emergency distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Emergency stop:
                  Trigger: obstacle detected within emergency distance.
                  Effect: immediate motor_set(0,0); path execution aborted; MC_PathExecutionStatus updated accordingly.
                - Inability to find avoidance maneuver:
                  Trigger: all nearby configurations violate minimum clearance M.
                  Effect: stay stopped, report failure and rely on higher-level replanning or manual recovery.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--RUN--1.1.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1 LL--INTERF--1.2.2
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2 LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--9</ID>
            <Name>Pose Estimation Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains discrete cell-level pose estimate:
                - Integrates differential drive kinematics over control loop periods.
                - Estimates current cell index (row, col) and discrete heading aligned with maze axes.
                - Corrects accumulated errors using detected walls and alignment.
                - Detects transitions between cell centers and notifies mapping module.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current pose estimate including:
                                - Cell indices (row, col).
                                - Discrete heading index ∈ {NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, WEST}.
                                - Continuous pose (x,y,θ) in maze frame if needed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>CellCenterEntryEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event fired when pose crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center.
                                Contains new cell index and direction of motion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides duration T or measured cycle duration used for integration of motor commands.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseForMotionControl</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Detail of continuous pose and heading used by motion control to determine progress along primitives.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotionCommandedSpeeds</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Last-issued motor_set speeds for left and right wheels; used to integrate motion via kinematics.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseAlignedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag to mapping indicating when pose has been snapped to maze axes and is reliable for wall mapping decisions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to correct pose when walls indicate proximity to known cell boundaries; align orientation and position to nearest consistent cell center.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Use last cycle's motor speed commands and loop duration T to integrate differential drive kinematics:
                   - Update continuous pose (x,y,θ).
                2) Map continuous pose to discrete cell indices using grid coordinate system and cell dimension 17.2 cm.
                3) If near theoretical cell center and heading near axis-aligned directions:
                   - Snap heading to nearest axis orientation.
                   - Snap position to nearest cell center consistent with wall locations.
                4) Detect cell center transitions by comparing previous and current discrete cell indices.
                   - Emit CellCenterEntryEvent when crossing occurs.
                5) Provide PoseEstimate to consumers.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updates once per control loop after motion command is known.
                - Needs to complete before mapping and mission control use updated pose.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Discrete heading always one of four axis-aligned states.
                - PoseEstimate always maps to a valid cell within [0..3][0..7].
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Large discrepancy between pose and walls:
                  Handling: if no consistent cell center matches wall observations, keep last valid discrete pose and flag degraded pose quality for mapping.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--POSE--1.1.1 LL--POSE--1.1.2 LL--POSE--1.1.3
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.2.1
                LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--10</ID>
            <Name>Scheduler and Initialization</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides main control loop timing and initialization signaling:
                - Implements periodic control loop at configurable period T.
                - Coordinates execution order: sensor sampling, map update, mission control, planning, motion control.
                - After init, raises INIT_COMPLETED indication.
                - Ensures sensor sampling rate equals control loop frequency.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Clock tick for each control loop iteration:
                                - Used by SAL, motion control, pose estimation to advance state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_Config</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration of sampling rate within [10, 50] Hz, default 20 Hz, used to determine T.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>InitCompletedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Binary flag/event set after all hardware and software initialization routines have been executed successfully.
                                Mission control reads this to leave IDLE state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>HardwareInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Results of hardware initialization routines.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - At startup:
                  1) Run hardware and software initialization routines.
                  2) Initialize grid map, pose, sensors, motion control configurations.
                  3) Set INIT_COMPLETED flag.
                - Periodic control loop (every T):
                  1) Emit Sched_ControlLoopTick.
                  2) Acquire sensor readings via SAL.
                  3) Update grid map via mapping and map module.
                  4) Update mission control state machine.
                  5) Trigger path planning for active state.
                  6) Execute motion control (issuing motor_set once per loop).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Control loop frequency equals configured sampling rate.
                - Jitter bounds derived from LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 must be met; scheduler ensures stable T.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Exactly one pass through the ordered steps per control loop iteration.
                - No concurrent execution of map access functions (single-threaded model).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Failure in initialization step:
                  Effect: INIT_COMPLETED not set; mission control remains in IDLE, robot not moving.
                - Timer overrun:
                  If a loop iteration exceeds T, scheduler records overrun and may extend next period or skip non-critical tasks like logging.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--11</ID>
            <Name>Exploration Status and Time Limit Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Monitors map completeness and exploration time to emit exploration status events:
                - Tracks elapsed exploration time.
                - Checks grid map completeness flag.
                - Emits EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events via system event queue.
                - Provides remaining exploration time to time-aware planning.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_MapCompletenessQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query of boolean map complete flag each control loop or at configured intervals.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indicating whether map is complete.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ExplorationEvents</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queue entries created when:
                                - Map completeness changes from false to true (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED).
                                - Elapsed exploration time exceeds 5 minutes (EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RemainingExplorationTimeInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                ElapsedTimeMs and RemainingTimeMs (5 min - ElapsedTimeMs) available to mission control and exploration modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_StateBroadcast</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to identify when EXPLORE starts/stops for time tracking (elapsed time measured only while in exploration phase or from exploration start as defined).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>TimeAwarePlanningInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Remaining exploration time and nominal cell traversal duration parameter exposed for frontier target selection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>NominalTraversalParam</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configurable parameter (ms per cell) used to convert path steps into estimated traversal times.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On entering EXPLORE:
                  - Record exploration start time (mission time).
                - Each control loop:
                  1) Compute elapsed exploration time from start time.
                  2) If elapsed &gt;= 5 minutes:
                     - Emit EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event exactly once.
                  3) If GM_MapCompletenessFlag is true and not yet signaled:
                     - Emit EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event exactly once.
                  4) Update RemainingExplorationTimeInfo for other modules.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Event checks happen once per control loop.
                - Uses scheduler-provided mission time or tick counts to compute elapsed time accurately.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and one EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event per mission.
                - RemainingTimeMs never negative; clamped at zero.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Time base failure (no time information):
                  Handling: treat as no remaining time; likely cause immediate timeout and safe return behavior.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.6 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>
    </Components>

    <StateMachines version="1">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Keep motors stopped (no MC_MotionCommand).
                        - Monitor INIT_COMPLETED and SensorAvailabilityStatus flags.
                        - Initialize exploration-related timers and flags upon future exit.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Periodically request frontier targets from CMP--2.
                        - Send MC_PathPlanningRequest to CMP--4 for selected frontier cell.
                        - If path available, issue MC_MotionCommand in exploration speed profile to CMP--8.
                        - Monitor ExplorationEvents and pose to detect exploration completion/timeout.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke return-to-start service: request path from current cell to start cell.
                        - Command motion control to execute return path.
                        - Monitor ReturnToStartStatus for completion or failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Request fastest path from start cell to selected goal region with time-optimized traversal cost.
                        - Command motion control to execute path with higher speed profile respecting safety.
                        - Monitor second run execution status to derive success/failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Cease issuing new MC_MotionCommand (motors left stopped by motion control).
                        - Maintain final second-run status in MC_SecondRunStatusOutput for external reporting.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        INIT_COMPLETED indication present AND SensorAvailabilityStatus is true, both sampled within control loop.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No critical errors in initialization.
                        - Map initialized with start cell set to FREE.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Reset exploration timers and elapsed time counters.
                        - Initialize exploration modules (frontier generation, exploration-status).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event OR
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event from exploration-status module, whichever occurs first.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Current motion commands are safe to stop or replan.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop issuing further frontier requests.
                        - Issue return-to-start path planning request from current cell to start cell.
                        - Set internal reason code (COMPLETED or TIMEOUT).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - ReturnToStartStatus indicates REACHED_START.
                        - Exploration previously declared complete (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event had occurred; TIMEOUT alone may still allow second run if map sufficient).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Robot pose at start cell (verified by pose estimate and possibly small tolerance).
                        - Start cell is FREE in map.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Request goal region identification/selection if not already done.
                        - Request fastest path plan (SECOND_RUN mode).
                        - Initialize MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to RUNNING.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        ReturnToStartStatus indicates PLANNING_FAILURE or ABORTED_COLLISION and no alternative route available.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Policy: mission ends if robot cannot return safely.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to FAILURE.
                        - Ensure motion commands are stopped.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == SUCCESS_REACHED_GOAL OR
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == FAILURE_COLLISION OR
                        - Planning failure for fastest path.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        None beyond trigger; any terminal status ends mission.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Latch MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to SUCCESS or FAILURE depending on reported status.
                        - Stop issuing path execution commands to motion control.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4
                LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3 LL--RUN--1.2.4 LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>
    </StateMachines>

    <AdditionalData version="1">
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--1</ID>
            <Content>
                Grid Map Data Structures:
                - Define:
                  enum CellState { CELL_UNKNOWN = 0, CELL_FREE = 1, CELL_BLOCKED = 2 };
                  enum WallState { WALL_UNKNOWN = 0, WALL_PRESENT = 1, WALL_ABSENT = 2 };
                - Cell storage:
                  CellState cells[4][8];
                - Wall storage:
                  - Horizontal walls between (row, col) and (row+1, col):
                    WallState hWalls[3][8];
                  - Vertical walls between (row, col) and (row, col+1):
                    WallState vWalls[4][7];
                - Coordinate convention (example):
                  - Row 0, Col 0 is start cell at bottom-left or a specified corner, as per HL environment.
                  All modules must consistently use this indexing.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--2</ID>
            <Content>
                Traversal Cost Model Parameters:
                - Define cost units such that:
                  baseStraightCost = 1.0 per move between adjacent FREE cells with no turn.
                  turnPenalty = configurable &gt;= 0 for turns between edges (e.g., 0.5).
                - Exploration profile:
                  - Emphasize information gain while maintaining reasonable path length; keep baseStraightCost small, turnPenalty modest.
                - Second-run profile:
                  - Set parameters corresponding to estimated travel time:
                    costPerStraightCell = cellLength / nominalSpeed.
                    costPerTurn = extra time to decelerate, turn, accelerate.
                - Cost computation:
                  For each path:
                    TotalCost = sum(edgeCosts) where edgeCost = baseStraightCost (+turnPenalty when heading changes).
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.5 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--3</ID>
            <Content>
                Time-Aware Planning and Nominal Cell Traversal Duration:
                - Configuration parameter:
                  uint32_t nominalCellTraversalMs; // default derived from measured robot speed at exploration speed.
                - Remaining exploration time:
                  remainingTimeMs = max(0, explorationTimeLimitMs - elapsedExplorationMs).
                - Frontier feasibility test:
                  For candidate frontier at distance N_cells from current cell:
                    estTravelMs = N_cells * nominalCellTraversalMs;
                    estMappingOverheadMs = nominalCellTraversalMs; // simple fixed overhead.
                    If estTravelMs + estMappingOverheadMs &gt; remainingTimeMs, discard candidate.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3 LL--MAP--1.1.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--4</ID>
            <Content>
                Ultrasonic Uncertainty and Clearance Checks:
                - Ultrasonic measurement model:
                  Each distance reading d_cm is expanded to [d_cm - 12, d_cm + 12] cm interval.
                - Robot model:
                  Radius R = 5.5 cm.
                  Wall thickness ~1.6 cm.
                  Cell size L = 17.2 cm.
                - Expected center-to-wall distance for front wall when centered in cell:
                  approxDistance = L/2 + wallThickness/2 ≈ 8.6 + 0.8 = 9.4 cm (approximate; derived precisely in implementation).
                - Clearance margin M:
                  Configurable M &gt; 0 cm, e.g., 2–5 cm; planned trajectories ensure robot center stays at least R + M away from any wall boundary.
                - Emergency stop threshold:
                  Derived from maximum speed, stopping distance, and uncertainty interval; ensures robot can stop before wall even in worst-case measurement error.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1 LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--ENV--1.3.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--5</ID>
            <Content>
                Sensor Filtering and Consistency Parameters:
                - Sampling frequency:
                  configurable in [10, 50] Hz; default 20 Hz.
                  controlLoopPeriod T = 1 / samplingFrequency.
                - Filter windows:
                  ultrasonicMovingAverageWindow = 3–5 samples.
                  IRmovingAverageOrDebounceWindow = 2–3 samples.
                - Consistency threshold N for changing map entries from FREE/ABSENT to BLOCKED/PRESENT:
                  integer N ∈ [2, 10], default 3.
                  Implementation: maintain counters per cell/wall; only change classification when N consecutive readings indicate a change.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--6</ID>
            <Content>
                Motion Primitive Specification:
                - Straight move primitive:
                  Move from one cell center to adjacent in direction of current discrete heading.
                  Steps:
                  1) Compute distance to travel = cellLength (17.2 cm).
                  2) Compute required duration based on exploration or second-run speed (cm/s).
                  3) Execute repeated motor_set commands with equal left/right speeds for computed number of control loop cycles.
                - Turn in place primitive:
                  Rotate by ±90° or 180° to align with maze axis.
                  Use differential drive kinematics to determine wheel speeds and duration for desired angle based on robot geometry.
                - Arc turn primitive for avoidance:
                  Use left/right speeds with appropriate ratio to follow circular arc of radius &gt;= R + M to maintain clearance from walls.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2 LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--MAP--1.2.4 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--7</ID>
            <Content>
                Event Queue for Exploration and Mission Events:
                - Data structure:
                  Circular buffer of fixed size (e.g., 16 entries) storing:
                  struct Event { EventType type; uint32_t timestamp; EventPayload payload; };
                - Supported event types include:
                  EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT, PATH_INVALIDATED, RETURN_COMPLETED, SECOND_RUN_COMPLETED.
                - Usage:
                  - Modules (e.g., exploration-status) enqueue events.
                  - Mission control dequeues and processes all available events each control loop.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
    </AdditionalData>
</Design>

