        <Description>
            CMP--11 defines ExplorationEvents and RemainingExplorationTimeInfo transmitted to CMP--1, and TimeAwarePlanningInfo transmitted to CMP--2, but:
            - CMP--1’s ConnectedComponents do not include CMP--11 as a peer, even though CMP--1 claims to Receive ExplorationEvents.
            - CMP--2’s TimeAwarePlanningInfo Receive is currently declared under the ConnectedComponent with Identifier CMP--3, which is incorrect; the provider is CMP--11.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            - Add a ConnectedComponent with Identifier CMP--11 in CMP--1’s ConnectedComponents, with Receive ExplorationEvents and RemainingExplorationTimeInfo as appropriate.
            - In CMP--2, move TimeAwarePlanningInfo to a ConnectedComponent with Identifier CMP--11 (or add one if missing).
        </Solution>
    </Finding>

    <Finding ID="DESIGN--1--10">
        <ItemID>FSM--1</ItemID>
        <Severity>Minor</Severity>
        <Description>
            FSM--1 transitions mention “return-to-start service” and “second-run planning service” but there are no corresponding components named as such; the actual services appear to be implemented by CMP--4 (planner), CMP--8 (motion), CMP--5 (goal region), and CMP--11 (events). This can make traceability from state-machine behavior to concrete components ambiguous.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            Clarify within FSM--1 (e.g. in StateActions or TransitionAction text) which specific components are invoked for each service, using their component IDs (CMP--4/CMP--8/CMP--5/CMP--11). Alternatively, define explicit subcomponents or service labels and map them back to the existing components in the design description.
        </Solution>
    </Finding>

    <Finding ID="DESIGN--1--11">
        <ItemID>CMP--2</ItemID>
        <Severity>Minor</Severity>
        <Description>
            In CMP--2’s DerivedFrom list, LL--MAP--1.1.6 appears twice. This is a minor documentation redundancy that may cause confusion in traceability tooling.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            Remove the duplicate LL--MAP--1.1.6 entry from the DerivedFrom list for CMP--2, keeping only a single occurrence.
        </Solution>
    </Finding>

    <Finding ID="DESIGN--1--12">
        <ItemID>DAT--1</ItemID>
        <Severity>Minor</Severity>
        <Description>
            DAT--1 describes grid map data structures and coordinate conventions but does not explicitly state how the fixed start cell coordinate from LL--MAP--1.3.4 and LL--ENV--1.1.1 is selected (e.g., “row 0, col 0 at bottom-left” vs. other corners). The text says “bottom-left or a specified corner”, which leaves ambiguity.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            Fix a single, explicit convention (e.g., “row 0, col 0 is the start cell at the bottom-left corner of the maze as seen from the robot’s starting orientation”) and state it unambiguously in DAT--1 so that all mapping, planning, and control modules can rely on it.
        </Solution>
    </Finding>

    <Finding ID="DESIGN--1--13">
        <ItemID>CMP--3</ItemID>
        <Severity>Minor</Severity>
        <Description>
            CMP--3’s Invariants and DerivedFrom combine both LL--MAP--1.3.5 and LL--MAP--1.4.1/1.4.2 static-map assumptions, but the Execution section does not explicitly indicate how attempts from consistency checks (LL--RELIAB--1.2.2) to change FREE/ABSENT back to a wall-present state are handled beyond “reject update”. There is no explicit link to consistency counters or N-consecutive-evidence requirement.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            Add a short note in CMP--3 Execution or Failures explaining that callers (e.g., CMP--6) are required to perform N-consecutive consistency checks before issuing MM_MapUpdateRequest that would conflict with current FREE/ABSENT states, and that CMP--3 enforces immutability by rejecting any such conflicting update. Optionally reference DAT--5 in this explanation.
        </Solution>
    </Finding>
</Findings>
